President Donald Trump has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to attend the opening of the United States Embassy in Jerusalem, Israel on May 14, 2018. The delegation will be led by Deputy Secretary of State John Sullivan and includes United States Ambassador to Israel David Friedman, Secretary of the Treasury Steven Mnuchin, Senior Advisor to the President Jared Kushner, Advisor to the President Ivanka Trump, and Special Representative for International Negotiations Jason Greenblatt.